1.title: Solace at the Supermarket

episode of.title: Wholesome Foods I Love You... Is That OK? (TV Series 2018– )

1.plot: Julia, a lovably neurotic yoga teacher whose life is a total disaster sets out in search of love - at her favorite organic supermarket. But does she get more than she's bargained for?

2.title: The Patron Saint of Leftovers

episode of.title: Wholesome Foods I Love You... Is That OK? (TV Series 2018– )

2.plot: Julia fills her roommates in on her awkward romantic run-in at the organic market. She returns to the market the next day hoping for another chance run-in - little does she know that Marko's hoping for exactly the same thing.

3.title: The Seven Wonders of the Secret Spice World

episode of.title: Wholesome Foods I Love You... Is That OK? (TV Series 2018– )

3.plot: After an upsetting meeting with her PhD thesis advisor and an unexpected incident in the street, Julia seeks advice from her mentor and employer, the self-absorbed yoga studio owner, Shakti. She wraps up her day at - where else?... Wholesome Foods Market - where she chats up her favorite regular customers and gets to know a little about Marko's personal life.

4.title: I Don't Feel Compassionate Today

episode of.title: Wholesome Foods I Love You... Is That OK? (TV Series 2018– )

4.plot: Julia pays her sister a visit in hopes of getting a little help with her rent situation. She pops into the yoga studio, only to get a text from Alex about a roommate-related bacon situation that needs her attention STAT.

5.title: His Name Is Salmon

episode of.title: Wholesome Foods I Love You... Is That OK? (TV Series 2018– )

5.plot: Julia and Cartwright run into Marko at the store, and ask him to settle an on-going argument. Cartwright eventually gives up, heading outside to work on his "beats". Curious, Marko asks Julia to take him outside to listen to what "the real Slim Shady" has to offer up.

6.title: Cash Out Tuna

episode of.title: Wholesome Foods I Love You... Is That OK? (TV Series 2018– )

6.plot: Julia teaches Marko how to find the best bite of an apple and explains Ayurvedic medicine. Cartwright joins the roommates for a CrossFit workout while the girls talk about metaphysical things.

7.title: Because They Look Like Kundalini Yogis

episode of.title: Wholesome Foods I Love You... Is That OK? (TV Series 2018– )

7.plot: Jai explains why her guac fast has to come to an end. Julia talks about what it's like to be a highly sensitive person, while Marko tries to teach her about basketball.

8.title: Store Policy Review

episode of.title: Wholesome Foods I Love You... Is That OK? (TV Series 2018– )

8.plot: After Julia and Marko sneak off to spy on a staff meeting at the market, things start to heat up and get ultra personal between them.

9.title: Supermarket Savasanahhh

episode of.title: Wholesome Foods I Love You... Is That OK? (TV Series 2018– )

9.plot: Marko fumbles through an Izzy-related crisis and almost gets caught by Julia. Startled, he picks a fight, upsetting Julia. To make it up to her, he offers to do yoga with her.

10.title: Got Camels?

episode of.title: Wholesome Foods I Love You... Is That OK? (TV Series 2018– )

10.plot: Confused about why things seem to be falling apart with Marko, Julia asks the universe for a very specific sign to help clear things up. When she starts seeing it everywhere, she sets out in search of Marko, but he's nowhere to be found...

11.title: Looking for Love in the Gluten-Free Snack Aisle

episode of.title: Wholesome Foods I Love You... Is That OK? (TV Series 2018– )

11.plot: Still feeling pretty confused, Julia sets up a private meditation session with Salmon. When the meeting is interrupted by a phone call from Marko, Julia suddenly finds herself picking a huge fight with him. Ah, sabotage... it gets to even the most devout of yogis every once in a while.

12.title: I Have a No-Asking-Guys-On-Dates Policy

imdb.plot outline: "WFILY" is the 3-time Indie Series Awards nominated offbeat dramedy about a neurotic yoga teacher who, in an effort to pick up the pieces of her ever-unraveling life, sets out in search of love - at her favorite organic supermarket. A coming of age story - for people of a certain age - Wholesome Foods, I Love You - Is That OK? reminds us all that love, laughter, and a willingness take risks are the best remedies of all.
